Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Input Parameters (optional)", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8824471684736547`*^9, 3.882447173074892*^9}, {
  3.9844796263627567`*^9, 
  3.98447963008587*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d116fbb0-609f-4975-bc8e-\
4ac825a670fd"],

Cell["\<\
Input parameter section:  {pdb,itp}. Not necessary but can make building a \
complex molecule easier to follow.
Special bond connections can be input here.
MX defines pdb and itp inputs for a monomer
bXY defines bond connections {a,b,c}, where X is the residue described and Y \
is the residue number the residue is connected to. 
See notes for function \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]addNextMonomer\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote].\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.883229189508874*^9, 3.8832291964493504`*^9}, {
